  <how_to_use_section>
    <how_to_use>
      <title>Add layer effects animation functionality to ArcMap</title>
      <how_to_use_steps>
        <step>Compile the sample project in Visual Studio.</step>
        <step>Start ArcMap and add a raster layer to the table of contents (TOC).</step>
        <step>Click Customize, Toolbars, and Animation to open the Animation toolbar.</step>
        <step>You can now create layer effects animation in ArcMap in a similar way as you create a map layer animation (first use the Create Animation Keyframe dialog box to create a layer effects track with two keyframes, then use the Animation Manager to set the keyframe properties).</step>
      </how_to_use_steps>
    </how_to_use>
